  2→//!
  3→//! Setup files are Rust source files compiled to binaries and executed as
  4→//! subprocesses. The subprocess receives setup parameters as JSON on stdin
  5→//! and returns a JSON context object on stdout. This context is passed to
  6→//! subsequent Execute commands so frontends can restore setup state.
